# ERP Intelligence Layer — Implementation Plan

## Goal

Transform OPS//CORE from a standalone CSV-driven planning system into an **ERP integration layer** that can **Read**, **Write**, **Listen**, and **Explain** against enterprise ERPs (SAP, Oracle, Odoo) — while keeping the current CSV mode as the default demo/fallback.

The sales pitch: *"We don't replace your ERP — we make it intelligent."*

---

## Current Architecture (What We Have)

```mermaid
graph LR
    CSV["data.csv (2.5M rows)"] --> LoadDF["_load_df()"]
    LoadDF --> Orchestrator
    Orchestrator --> Forecaster & Mechanic & Buyer & Environ & Finance & Scheduler
    Orchestrator --> Cache["_CACHE → REST API"]
    Cache --> Frontend
```

**Key constraint**: Every agent receives `context["df"]` — a pandas DataFrame sliced from `data.csv`. Agents never query the database directly for production data. This is the **single integration point** we need to intercept.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is a demo/hackathon architecture.** We simulate ERP connectivity using a pluggable adapter pattern. A real SAP RFC/BAPI integration requires an SAP account, `pyrfc`, and SAP credentials. This plan creates the **adapter interface + mock adapters** so the architecture is enterprise-ready, and the demo shows a convincing ERP integration flow without requiring actual ERP credentials.

> [!WARNING]
> **No external ERP accounts are assumed.** The plan uses mock adapters that generate realistic data matching SAP/Odoo schemas. If you have access to an Odoo instance, the Odoo adapter can be made live with minimal changes.

