## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: ERP Adapter Layer (Backend)

The core abstraction — a pluggable connector that standardises how OPS//CORE talks to any ERP.

---

#### [NEW] [erp_adapter.py](file:///c:/Users/Charan/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/CBIT/backend/erp_adapter.py)

**Abstract base class** defining the 4 capabilities:

```python
class ERPAdapter(ABC):
    # ── READ ──
    def pull_inventory(plant_id) -> list[dict]        # Live stock levels
    def pull_open_orders(plant_id) -> list[dict]       # Open sales/production orders
    def pull_bom(product_id) -> dict                   # Bill of Materials
    def pull_machine_status(plant_id) -> list[dict]    # Machine OEE, temp, vibration

    # ── WRITE ──
    def push_production_order(order: dict) -> dict     # Create/update prod order in ERP
    def push_purchase_order(po: dict) -> dict          # Create PO in ERP for reorders
    
    # ── LISTEN ──
    def poll_events(since: datetime) -> list[dict]     # Poll for new ERP events
    
    # ── EXPLAIN ──
    def generate_audit_link(action_id: str) -> str     # Deep-link back to OPS//CORE rationale
```

Each method returns standardised dicts regardless of which ERP is behind it.

