### Component 2: ERP Audit Trail & Explain

Every action OPS//CORE pushes to the ERP is logged with full rationale traceability.

---

#### [NEW] [erp_audit.py](file:///c:/Users/Charan/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/CBIT/backend/erp_audit.py)

- New SQLite table `erp_audit_log`:
  ```
  id, timestamp, erp_type, action_type, document_id, idempotency_key,
  agent_name, run_id, rationale, payload_before, payload_after, status, erp_response
  ```
- **Idempotency**: Before every write, check if `idempotency_key` already exists → skip duplicate pushes
- **Rationale link**: Every audit row stores the `run_id` + `agent_name` so the frontend can deep-link to the Agent Reasoning page showing exactly why the decision was made
- `generate_explain_url(audit_id)` → returns `/agent-reasoning?run_id=xxx&highlight=agent`

