### Component 3: Event Listener (Backend)

Subscribes to ERP events and triggers re-planning when relevant changes occur.

---

#### [NEW] [erp_listener.py](file:///c:/Users/Charan/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/CBIT/backend/erp_listener.py)

- Background async loop (similar to `_agent_loop`) that polls `adapter.poll_events()` every N seconds
- Event types handled:
  | ERP Event | OPS//CORE Action |
  |---|---|
  | New Sales Order | Trigger Forecaster re-run, update demand context |
  | Goods Receipt | Update inventory levels, cancel pending reorders |
  | PO Confirmation | Mark Buyer reorder as fulfilled |
  | Machine Status Change | Trigger Mechanic re-assessment |
- Each event is logged to a new `erp_events` SQLite table
- Events that require re-planning set a flag that the `_agent_loop` checks

